ğŸ”¹ Description
Designed and deployed a secure, AI-powered Visitor Management System to replace manual visitor registers with a fully automated digital platform. The system enables face-based identity verification, real-time host notifications, appointment booking, and secure check-in/check-out. The entire application was containerized using Docker to ensure consistent, scalable, and production-ready deployments across environments.

ğŸ”¹ Key Contributions & Responsibilities
â€¢ Designed and developed full-stack architecture using React (Frontend), Node.js/Express (Backend), and MongoDB (Database)
â€¢ Built RESTful APIs for visitor registration, authentication, logging, and notifications
â€¢ Implemented AI-based Face Recognition using OpenCV + FaceNet with embedding comparison for accurate visitor verification
â€¢ Integrated JWT-based authentication for secure API access and session management
â€¢ Configured Nginx reverse proxy with SSL/TLS for secure HTTPS communication
â€¢ Containerized backend, database, and Python ML services using Docker & Docker Compose
â€¢ Managed backend processes using PM2 for high availability and zero-downtime restarts
â€¢ Automated deployment setup on Linux VPS servers
â€¢ Applied security best practices including UFW firewall, server hardening, and environment isolation
â€¢ Implemented real-time visitor logs, notifications, and reporting features
â€¢ Collaborated on testing, debugging, and performance optimization

